\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 10. THE BANKING INTEREST CALCULATOR\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 Scenario:
\f2\b0  A bank manages different types of accounts with different interest rules. 
\f1\b Task:
\f2\b0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 a) Create a base class 
\f1\b 'BankAccount'
\f2\b0  with a method 
\f1\b 'applyInterest()'
\f2\b0 .\
\ls2\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 b) Create subclasses 
\f1\b 'SavingsAccount'
\f2\b0  and 
